body:
Sigh…

Sooooo, a few months ago, I started up a separate blog, for the Ikariverse. It’s called @asktheaggretsukofam. If you want, check it out, you can ask questions to Retsuko, Haida, Ikari, even Fenneko.

Anyways, one such question came my way: “when is Ikari’s birthday?” Keep in mind, this was months ago. I kinda just decided to put a date I figured would be nice to have. I wrote something down in June, and left it at that. Just earlier today, I remembered that question, and decided to look back at it. After all, June IS coming up, figured I might as well get the party goin’.

And….well….

Sooooo, yeah. Ikari’s birthday is June 15th….one whole day after Season 2 drops. Figured I might as well tell y’all now, both in case people wanna give birthday wishes to the dear bon-bon boi, and…..well, to be honest, if Season 2 ends a certain way, I think I might need some of those, to cheer me up. 🙃

summary:
WHAT’S HAPPENIN’ YA CLOWNS?
Let’s get fuckin’ WEEEEEEIRD for a minute. Let’s go into almost conspiracy levels of off the deep...
body:
WHAT’S HAPPENIN’ YA CLOWNS?

Let’s get fuckin’ WEEEEEEIRD for a minute. Let’s go into almost conspiracy levels of off the deep end!

Okay, that was a weird way to start this up, but hear me out! I got something both kinda funny, kinda weird, and kinda…worthy of fan-art-ish.

I’ve joked before, in regards to Aggretsuko, that Retsuko’s death metal voice should’ve instead been done by Alissa White-Gluz, the current vocalist for Swedish melodic death metal band Arch Enemy.

If you wanna good glimpse of what she sounds like, here’s a music video from their most recent album: https://youtu.be/lk2-bgwA0Ro

So, at first, I just left it at that. Seemed like a silly joke, yet cool idea. Then, just a few weeks ago, I was browsing Instagram (heh, how fitting, knowing the show, eh?), and just randomly came across Alissa’s page….and I found out something that hit me like a freight train.

She’s actually going out with Doyle Wolfgang von Frankenstein, the guitarist for the band, The Misfits.

The Misfits are a horror punk band.

Horror punk.

Punk.

So, like, female death metal singer, in a relationship with a guitarist of a punk band.

To add to that, not only can he play guitar…

He can play bass too.

Not to mention:

He’s a bit of a tall, sulky dude.

Almost like…

H-hold on a minute, I-

W-WAIT A GODDAMN SEC-

summary: So I finally got around to remembering I had the Aggretsuko candy bar after the midst of a PMS-induced chocolate craving. Rest...
body:
So I finally got around to remembering I had the Aggretsuko candy bar after the midst of a PMS-induced chocolate craving. Rest assured I just took a bite…for now. (ﾉ´ヮ`)ﾉ*: ･ﾟ💝🍫 It’s a nice and tangy ( albeit bland in terms of the chocolate itself) wrapped in gold foil that was produced by the Chocolate Lab in Hollywood! Right next to the Chinese Theater.

Weight: 6 oz

Ingredients: Dark chocolate infused with chocolate hazelnut cream, potato chips, chili powder and sea salt. Mildly bitter sweet/ tangy flavor.

The design is super lovely! 💖 However, I wish they added indent lines on the bar so you could break off the pieces neatly. Overall, I can understand the price ( $8 USD ) because its made from a luxury choco brand in Hollywood. But still, I wish they had more variation for candies for her.
